EntityInstance.DEFINITION: A set of 57 instructions built into some versions of central processors units for supporting SIMD operations on multimedia and communications data types.
A processor whose design is based on the rapid execution of a sequence of simple instructions rather than on the provision of a large variety of complex instructions.
A processor where each instruction can perform several low-level operations such as memory access, arithmetic operations or address calculations.
A physical component that is an assembly can have other assemblies and parts as sub-components.
The functional component in the association that performs a particular function for a physical component.
A component can require other functional components. This is a shared component. E.g. a laptop requires a hard disk to operate. Software also requires a hard disk to operate.
The physical component in the association that implements a particular function.
A constraining association between components that denotes the capability of the source component to be able to satisfy the functional requirements of the destination component.

The recommended association is a constraining heuristic that provides some indication of optional configuration for performing a function. For example, a specific processor clock rate will be recommended for a computer configuration that is needs to execute a particular software package.
A component can provide other functional components. E.g. a laptop provides a serial port.
A component can exclusively require another functional component in order for it to operate. E.g. a memory slot is exclusively required by a memory module. The slot cannot be shared.
